         <abstract>
            <p>Multiply schemes are used as a model of a linear congruential scheme. It is suggested how the properties of linear congruential schemes as pseudo-random number generators might be improved by shuffling. Asymptotic frequencies of pairs and triples from multiply schemes are obtained.</p>
          </abstract>
